                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 European War 1939/21452: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Consul General at Algiers (<persName type="to">Cole</persName>)</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-05-07T22:00:00-04:00"
                            >May 7, 1942—10 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>132. For Murphy from the Under Secretary. Your 296 of May 5 [<hi rend="italic"
                        >6</hi>], 8 p.m., has been duly received and is having close study. When
                    this is completed and after a final consultation I shall endeavor to reply as
                    definitely as possible. [Welles.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
